        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-12-15T09:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-12-15T09:36:00-05:00" n="313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <head>313. Backchannel Message From the Ambassador to Pakistan (<persName
                        corresp="#p_FJS1" type="from">Farland</persName>) to the Presidentʼs
                    Assistant for National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1" type="to"
                        >Kissinger</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d313fn1">Source:
                        National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential
                        Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 426, Backchannel
                        Files, Backchannel Messages 1971, Amb. <persName corresp="#p_FJS1"
                            >Farland</persName>, Pakistan. Top Secret; Exclusive; Eyes Only. A
                        handwritten note on the message, in an unknown hand, reads: “briefed
                            <persName corresp="#p_HGAMJ1">Haig</persName>.” Copies were sent to
                            <persName corresp="#p_HGAMJ1">Haig</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_SHH1">Saunders</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Islamabad</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1971-12-15T14:36:00+00:00">December 15, 1971,
                        1436Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1096. Foreign Secretary called me to Foreign Office 1800 local 15 December. Said
                    reports received from <persName corresp="#p_BZA1">Bhutto</persName> indicate he
                    highly pessimistic that any affirmative action will be forthcoming from Security
                    Council. In addition, <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> intelligence indicates
                        <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> upping offensive activity against West
                    Pakistan and instigating subversive activity (presumably in Pushtun border
                    areas) out of Afghanistan. He said that for West Pakistan to survive as nation
                    it is necessary it be provided additional fighter aircraft. Present trickle
                    MIG–19s and F–104s (he did not indicate origin) cannot stem the tide if India
                    attacks—an attack which Pakistan now expects.</p>
            </div>
